<paragraph id="8BEF36EAFFAEFF9BFF259B84E093A772" blockId="10.[151,1436,1425,2026]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
The 
<typeStatus id="54EB8848FFAEFF9BFF799B87E1AFA5ED" box="[203,251,1426,1450]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFAEFF9BFEC99B86E0E4A5ED" box="[379,432,1427,1450]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Puto" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAEFF9BFEC99B86E0E4A5ED" box="[379,432,1427,1450]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Puto</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, now called 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFAEFF9BFDF09B86E202A5EE" authority="Signoret" authorityName="Signoret" box="[578,854,1425,1450]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Puto" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennatus">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAEFF9BFDF09B86E38EA5ED" box="[578,730,1427,1450]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P. antennatus</emphasis>
(Signoret)
</taxonomicName>
, was described by Signoret from female specimens collected on 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFAEFF9BFE9A9BA2E090A589" box="[296,452,1462,1486]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cembra">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAEFF9BFE9A9BA2E090A589" box="[296,452,1462,1486]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Pinus cembra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFAEFF9BFE619BA0E36EA58A" box="[467,570,1461,1485]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Pinaceae</taxonomicName>
) at Briançon and male specimens from 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFAEFF9BFC4D9BA3E5F9A589" box="[1023,1197,1462,1486]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pectinata">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAEFF9BFC4D9BA3E5F9A589" box="[1023,1197,1462,1486]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Abies pectinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFAEFF9BFB0F9BA0E470A58A" box="[1213,1316,1461,1485]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Pinaceae</taxonomicName>
) at Chambéry, both from the French Alps (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B1BFFAEFF9BFDAE9BCCE3E6A5B6" author="Reyne" box="[540,690,1497,1521]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Reyne, A. (1954) A redescription of Puto antennatus Sign. (Homoptera: Coccoidea) with notes on Ceroputo pilosellae Sulc and Macrocerococcus superbus Leon. Zoologische Mededelingen, 32, 291 - 324." type="journal article" year="1954">
Reyne, 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAEFF9BFDC49BCCE3E6A5B6" box="[630,690,1497,1521]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1954.0">1954</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B1BFFAEFF9BFD759BCFE237A5B6" author="Reyne" box="[711,867,1497,1522]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Reyne, A. (1954) A redescription of Puto antennatus Sign. (Homoptera: Coccoidea) with notes on Ceroputo pilosellae Sulc and Macrocerococcus superbus Leon. Zoologische Mededelingen, 32, 291 - 324." type="journal article" year="1954">
Reyne (
<number id="3D9824CDFFAEFF9BFC939BCCE20FA5B6" box="[801,859,1497,1521]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1954.0">1954</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
produced a detailed redescription of most instars based on Signoret’s 
<typeStatus id="54EB8848FFAEFF9BFECC9BEBE0FAA651" box="[382,430,1534,1558]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
material plus additional specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F347767AFFAEFF9BFC3A9BEBE280A652" box="[904,980,1534,1557]" name="France" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">France</collectingCountry>
and Bavaria, and provided notes on the biology of the species. The adult males described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B1BFFAEFF9BFD5E9837E2D1A67E" author="Reyne" box="[748,901,1569,1594]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Reyne, A. (1954) A redescription of Puto antennatus Sign. (Homoptera: Coccoidea) with notes on Ceroputo pilosellae Sulc and Macrocerococcus superbus Leon. Zoologische Mededelingen, 32, 291 - 324." type="journal article" year="1954">
Reyne (
<number id="3D9824CDFFAEFF9BFCF19834E229A67E" box="[835,893,1569,1593]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1954.0">1954</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
have 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAEFF9BFC7B9834E2B1A67E" box="[969,997,1569,1593]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="12.0">12</number>
eyes on the head and the aedeagus is a curved rod with a rounded apex. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFAEFF9BFD269852E20FA619" authority="Leonardi, 1907" authorityName="Leonardi" authorityYear="1907" box="[660,859,1607,1630]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Macrocerococcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAEFF9BFD269852E20FA619" box="[660,859,1607,1630]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Macrocerococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was erected for a species, now called 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFAEFF9BFAAB9852E046A6C6" authority="Leonardi" authorityName="Leonardi" authorityYear="1907" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Macrocerococcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="superbus">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAEFF9BFAAB9852E4C8A619" box="[1305,1436,1606,1630]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P. superbus</emphasis>
(Leonardi)
</taxonomicName>
, described from Sardinia but now considered a polyphagous species distributed throughout much of the Palaearctic Region (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B1BFFAEFF9BFEC89898E36CA6E2" author="Lagowska" box="[378,568,1677,1701]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Lagowska, B. (2000) Puto superbus (Leonardi, 1907) (Homoptera: Pseudococcidae) new to the Polish fauna. Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne, 69, 3 - 6." type="journal article" year="2000">
Łagowska, 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAEFF9BFE4F9898E36CA6E2" box="[509,568,1677,1701]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B1BFFAEFF9BFDF6989BE2D4A6E2" author="Marotta" box="[580,896,1677,1701]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Marotta, S. &amp; Tranfaglia, A. (1993) Le specie del genere Puto Signoret (Homoptera Coccoidea Pseudococcidae) del'Europa centrale e del bacino del Mediterraneo. Bollettino del Laboratorio di Entomologia Agraria ' Filippo Silvestri', Portici, 48, 171 - 205." type="journal article" year="1993">
Marotta &amp; Tranfaglia, 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAEFF9BFCF69898E2D4A6E2" box="[836,896,1677,1701]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1993.0">1993</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B1BFFAEFF9BFC269898E57CA6E2" author="Ferris" box="[916,1064,1677,1701]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Ferris, G. F. (1950) Atlas of the Scale Insects of North America. Series V. The Pseudococcidae (Part 1). Palo Alto, California, Stanford University Press, 278 pp." type="book" year="1950">
Ferris (
<number id="3D9824CDFFAEFF9BFC579898E574A6E2" box="[997,1056,1677,1701]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1950.0">1950</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
treated the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFAEFF9BFB43989AE1E9A68D" authority="Leonardi, 1907" authorityName="Leonardi" authorityYear="1907" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Macrocerococcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAEFF9BFB43989AE1E9A68D" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Macrocerococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAEFF9BFE7D98A6E35EA68D" box="[463,522,1715,1738]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFAEFF9BFE7D98A6E352A68D" box="[463,518,1715,1738]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Puto" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Puto</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and we agree with this synonymy. However, in agreement with 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B1BFFAEFF9BFB5098A7E438A68E" author="Tang" box="[1250,1388,1713,1738]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Tang, F. D. (1992) The Pseudococcidae of China (Homoptera: Coccinea of Insects). Beijing, Chinese Agricultural Science Technology Press, 767 pp." type="book" year="1992">
Tang (
<number id="3D9824CDFFAEFF9BFA9B98A4E430A68E" box="[1321,1380,1713,1737]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1992.0">1992</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B1BFFAEFF9BFF2598C0E028A6AA" box="[151,380,1749,1774]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Hardy, N. B., Gullan, P. J. &amp; Hodgson, C. J. (2008) A classification of mealybugs (Hemiptera: Coccoidea) based on integrated molecular and morphological data. Systematic Entomolog y, 33, 51 - 71." type="journal article">
Hardy 
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAEFF9BFF5A98C2E049A6A9" box="[232,285,1750,1774]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number id="3D9824CDFFAEFF9BFE8598C0E020A6AA" box="[311,372,1749,1773]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="2008.0">2008</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, we reject the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFAEFF9BFD6298C3E26CA6AA" authority="Šulc, 1897" authorityName="Šulc" authorityYear="1897" box="[720,824,1750,1773]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Ceroputo" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAEFF9BFD6298C3E26CA6AA" box="[720,824,1750,1773]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Ceroputo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFAEFF9BFC3298C2E2E1A6A9" box="[896,949,1751,1774]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Puto" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAEFF9BFC3298C2E2E1A6A9" box="[896,949,1751,1774]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Puto</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a taxonomic action attributable to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B1BFFAEFF9BFAE998C0E1B1A756" author="Ferris" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Ferris, G. F. (1918) The California species of mealy bugs. Leland Stanford Junior University Publications, University Series, Palo Alto, 78 pp." type="book" year="1918">
Ferris (
<number id="3D9824CDFFAEFF9BFF2D98ECE188A756" box="[159,220,1785,1809]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1918.0">1918</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. We also reject Kawai’s (
<number id="3D9824CDFFAEFF9BFE4F98ECE36CA756" box="[509,568,1785,1809]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1980.0">1980</number>
) synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFAEFF9BFD6D98EEE2F1A756" authority="Kanda" authorityName="Kanda" authorityYear="1959" box="[735,933,1785,1810]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Leococcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAEFF9BFD6D98EEE201A755" box="[735,853,1787,1810]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Leococcus</emphasis>
Kanda
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFAEFF9BFC5698EEE54DA755" box="[996,1049,1787,1810]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Puto" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAEFF9BFC5698EEE54DA755" box="[996,1049,1787,1810]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Puto</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as discussed below under the taxonomic notes on 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFAEFF9BFEE5990BE094A772" authority="Šulc, 1897" authorityName="Šulc" authorityYear="1897" box="[343,448,1822,1845]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Ceroputo" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAEFF9BFEE5990BE094A772" box="[343,448,1822,1845]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Ceroputo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36EAFFAEFF9AFF759954E30DA188" blockId="10.[151,1436,1425,2026]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,151,463]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="12" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAEFF9BFF759954E0E1A71D" bold="true" box="[199,437,1857,1882]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnostic features.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAEFF9BFE0C9957E31AA71D" box="[446,590,1858,1882]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Adult female</emphasis>
: eye height usually as great as length of first antennal segment; antennae usually with 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAEFF9BFE9E9970E06EA73A" box="[300,314,1893,1917]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="9.0">9</number>
segments, rarely with 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAEFF9BFDF09970E306A73A" box="[578,594,1893,1917]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="8.0">8</number>
; antennal intersegmental sensilla present between segments III–IV, IV–V and VI–VII; each surface of trochanter with 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAEFF9BFD21999CE3EAA7E6" box="[659,702,1929,1953]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5</number>
(usually 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAEFF9BFC9A999CE262A7E6" box="[808,822,1929,1953]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="3.0">3</number>
or 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAEFF9BFCEC999CE239A7E6" box="[862,877,1929,1953]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="4.0">4</number>
) campaniform sensilla; claw usually with pair of basal spurs; claw digitules often capitate but tarsal digitules almost never capitate; at least 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAEFF9BFB1899B8E592A782" box="[1194,1222,1965,1989]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="18.0">18</number>
pairs of cerarii on sclerotised plates, if more pairs present, increase due to division of cerarii on certain segments; long tubular ducts almost always present on frons (anterior to mouthparts); multilocular pores present on venter (except in 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFAFFF9AFA919E8CE19EA093" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Puto" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peyerinhoffi">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAFFF9AFA919E8CE19EA093" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. peyerinhoffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); quinquelocular pores absent (except in 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D69FFAFFF9AFD1D9EA8E201A093" box="[687,853,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Puto" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peyerinhoffi">
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAFFF9AFD1D9EA8E201A093" box="[687,853,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. peyerinhoffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); trilocular pores usually of 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAFFF9AFB149EA9E5E0A093" box="[1190,1204,188,212]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="3.0">3</number>
sizes, ventral pores smallest, dorsal pores noticeably larger, cerarian pores slightly larger than dorsal pores. 
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAFFF9AFBDA9EF5E416A0BF" box="[1128,1346,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Third-instar female</emphasis>
: resembles adult female but with 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAFFF9AFE7B9F11E081A15B" box="[457,469,260,284]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="8.0">8</number>
-segmented antennae, 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAFFF9AFD669F11E3AAA15B" box="[724,766,260,284]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
campaniform sensilla on each surface of trochanter, fewer pores and ducts and a non-functional vulva. 
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAFFF9AFD359F3CE236A107" box="[647,866,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">First-instar nymph:</emphasis>
<number id="3D9824CDFFAFFF9AFCD89F32E223A178" box="[874,887,295,319]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="7.0">7</number>
-segmented antennae; multilocular pores with&gt; 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAFFF9AFA3C9F32E4CFA178" box="[1422,1435,295,319]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="5.0">5</number>
loculi. 
<emphasis id="B924EAF8FFAFFF9AFF569F59E00AA123" box="[228,350,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Adult male</emphasis>
: row of 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAFFF9AFE0E9F59E0A0A123" box="[444,500,332,356]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="11.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="8.0">8–15</number>
(usually 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAFFF9AFDE99F59E32CA123" box="[603,632,332,356]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="14.0">14</number>
) eyes surrounding head, plus a pair of lateral ocelli; with one pair of lateral filaments near apex of abdomen (each filament from glandular pouch on each side of abdominal segment VIII); penial sheath 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAFFF9AFECB9F81E0D6A1EB" box="[377,386,404,428]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1.0">1</number>
-segmented, apex of aedeagus either bifid or simple (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B1BFFAFFF9AFC6B9F81E53FA1EB" author="Reyne" box="[985,1131,404,428]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Reyne, A. (1954) A redescription of Puto antennatus Sign. (Homoptera: Coccoidea) with notes on Ceroputo pilosellae Sulc and Macrocerococcus superbus Leon. Zoologische Mededelingen, 32, 291 - 324." type="journal article" year="1954">
Reyne, 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAFFF9AFB829F81E53FA1EB" box="[1072,1131,404,428]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1954.0">1954</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Beardsley, 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAFFF9AFB409F81E47AA1EB" box="[1266,1326,404,428]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1962.0">1962</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B1BFFAFFF9AFA8B9F81E067A188" author="Miller" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Miller, D. R. &amp; Miller, G. L. (1993 b) A new species of Puto and preliminary analysis of the phylogenetic position of the Puto group within the Coccoidea (Homoptera: Coccoidea). Jeffersoniana: Contributions from the Virginia Museum of Natural History, 4, 1 - 35." type="journal article" year="1993" yearSuffix="b">
Miller &amp; Miller, 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAFFF9AFF589FA2E070A188" box="[234,292,439,463]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1993.0">1993</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B1BFFAFFF9AFE8C9FA2E319A188" author="Hodgson" box="[318,589,439,463]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Hodgson, C. J. &amp; Foldi, I. (2006) A review of the Margarodidae sensu Morrison (Hemiptera: Coccoidea) and some related taxa based on the morphology of adult males. Zootaxa, 1263, 1 - 250." type="journal article" year="2006">
Hodgson &amp; Foldi, 
<number id="3D9824CDFFAFFF9AFDA29FA2E319A188" box="[528,589,439,463]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
